  <section>
    <title>Boom! Ireland is back!</title>
    <chapter>
      <paragraph>
        Ireland’s economic success wasn’t a given at all. The country was hit
        very hard by  he financial crisis and Great Recession: Irish banks were
        onthe verge of collapse, government debt skyrocketed, and unemployment
        topped 15%. Only a few years ago, experts warned that Ireland could be
        the “next Greece.” Ireland received international bailout loans in 2013,
        after its property market collapsed and banks started failing down.
      </paragraph>
    </chapter>
    <chapter>
      <paragraph>
        Unemployment went from 15% circa in 2011 to the actual 8.6%.
        In the same periode GDP growth from -5% in 2008, during Great
        Recession, to the 7% in 2015. For this year forecast is about 9%.
      </paragraph>
    </chapter>
